To clone a website using the provided Python script, you will need to install the following libraries:

    Flask: A web framework for building the web application.
        Install with pip install flask

    requests: A library for making HTTP requests to download web content.
        Install with pip install requests

    bs4 (Beautiful Soup): A library for parsing HTML and extracting data from it.
        Install with pip install beautifulsoup4
directory structure:
webclone/
├── webclone.py
├── templates/
│   └── index.html
├── js/
│   ├── script1.js
│   └── script2.js
├── css/
│   ├── style1.css
│   └── style2.css
├── sites/
│   └── cloned-web-paged.zip
└── images/
    ├── image1.jpg
    ├── image2.png
    └── ...
All cloned webpages are located in sites dir
